-- Owner of Islamic Channel Faces Defamation Charges, Ahram Says
-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 2012-09-16T08:10:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-16/owner-of-islamic-channel-faces-defamation-charges-ahram-says.html
The owner of  Egypt ’s al-Ummah
Islamic television channel was referred to the Supreme State
Security Prosecution on charges of religious defamation and
disturbing public peace and security, the state-run Al-Ahram
newspaper reported.  Ahmed Abdullah, also known as Sheikh Abu Islam, burned a
copy of the Bible during last week’s demonstrations at the U.S.
embassy in Cairo, Al-Ahram said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Cairo at 
 selwardany@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Digby Lidstone at 
 dlidstone@bloomberg.net  